race against time, Afro-Fabulations looks to the modes of memory and imagination through which a queer and black polytemporality is invented and sustained. Moving past the antirelational debates in queer theory, Nyong’o posits queerness as “angular sociality,” drawing upon queer of color critique in order to name the gate and rhythm of black social life as it moves in and out of step with itself. He takes up a broad range of sites of analysis, from speculative fiction to performance art, from artificial intelligence to Blaxploitation cinema. Reading the archive of violence and trauma against the grain, Afro-Fabulations summons the poetic powers of queer world-making that have always been immanent to the fight and play of black life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAfrican Americans in the performing arts. 0aAmerican dramaxAfrican American authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aGays in the performing artszUnited States. 0aHomosexuality in the theaterzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / African American Studies.2bisacsh  aAdrian Piper.  aAfrican diaspora.  aAnthropocene.  aBeasts of the Southern Wild.  aGalindo, Regina José.  aGeo Wyeth.  aGilles Deleuze.  aHarrell, Trajal.  aJason Holliday.  aJason and Shirley.  aKara Walker.  aManderlay.  aMandingo.  aMelvin van Peebles.  aParis Is Burning.  aPortrait of Jason.  aShirley Clarke.  aSweet Sweetback’s Baadasssss Song.  aThe Einstein Intersection.  aThe Flawless Mother Sabrina.  aThe Queen.  aWu Tsang.  aaesthetics.  aafrofuturism.  aantinormativity.  aarchives.  aartificial intelligence.  ablack art.  ablack code studies.  ablack performance.  ablack queer aesthetics.  ablack studies.  ablaxploitation.  abrownness.  achusmeria.  aclimate change.  acritical ethnic studies.  acu